# Trivy misconfiguration findings ignored for this repo.
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
#
# DS-0002 — "Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user as argument"
#
# Suppressed for `Dockerfile`: the image intentionally ships no USER directive
# because the entrypoint must start as root to
#   - chown the mounted /dockvol-data volume on first boot, and
#   - match the host Docker socket's group GID at runtime and add the dockvol
#     user to that group so the non-root app can read /var/run/docker.sock.
# It then drops privileges to the non-root dockvol user (UID 65532) via
# `exec gosu dockvol ./main` at the end of start.sh, so the app never runs as root.
DS-0002
